<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1339,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1411,1437]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[344,535,1411,1437]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Polemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[344,535,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Polemon collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a forest dwelling species found from 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1060,1411,1437]" name="Nigeria" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1094,1181,1411,1437]" name="Uganda" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Uganda</collectingCountry>
and south into western 
<collectingCountry box="[151,233,1447,1473]" name="Angola" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Angola</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Branch, W. R." box="[251,402,1447,1473]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="159" refId="ref34681" refString="Branch, W. R. (2018) Snakes of Angola: An annotated checklist. Amphibian &amp; Reptile Conservation, General Section, 12 (2), e 159, 41 - 82." type="journal article" year="2018">Branch 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[417,654,1447,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[525,584,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The label present in the jar reads “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1881" box="[1079,1293,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Microsoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collare">
<emphasis box="[1079,1293,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Microsoma collare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” but has no information regarding the collecting locality, however 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[768,939,1483,1510]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira (1906)</bibRefCitation>
cited an adult specimen of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bocage, J. V. B." box="[1251,1436,1483,1510]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref34376" refString="Bocage, J. V. B. (1895) Herpetologie d'Angola et du Congo. Ministerio da Marinha e das Colonias, Lisboa, 203 pp., 20 pls." type="book" year="1895">Bocage’s (1895)</bibRefCitation>
“form 
<emphasis box="[228,245,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">B</emphasis>
” from “Golungo Alto”, which most likely represents this specimen. After comparing Bocage’s original description and plate to MHNCUP/REP 170, we find the specimen to match the same morphology. 
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger, G. A." pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="105 - 115" refId="ref34581" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1905) A list of the batrachians and reptiles collected by Dr. W. J. Ansorge in Angola, with descriptions of new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 16 (92), 105 - 115, pl. 4. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443656" type="journal article" year="1905">Boulenger (1905)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="De Witte, G. - F. &amp; Laurent, R." box="[241,543,1591,1618]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref36794" refString="De Witte, G. - F. &amp; Laurent, R. (1947) Revision d'un groupe de Colubridae Africans genres Calamelaps, Miodon, Aparallactus et forms affines. Memoires de Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique, 2 (29), 1 - 134." type="journal article" year="1947">de Witte &amp; Laurent (1947)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hellmich, W." box="[599,786,1591,1618]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref38072" refString="Hellmich, W. (1957) Herpetologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise nach Angola. Veroffentlichungen der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen, 5, 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1957">Hellmich (1957)</bibRefCitation>
cited specimens from the same locality. Recently, Portilo 
<emphasis box="[151,208,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2018) reported a specimen from “North-west” 
<collectingCountry box="[749,834,1627,1653]" name="Angola" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Angola</collectingCountry>
, but according to Conradie (pers. comm.), the correct locality is “Camp Chiri, Saurimo Region, 
<collectingRegion box="[623,877,1663,1690]" country="Angola" name="Lunda Norte" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Lunda Norte Province</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
